AGI - The United States has announced new sanctions to impose on Iran. A decision taken following the attack by the Ayatollah regime against Israel on the evening of 13 April last. In addition to the words of the secretary of the Treasury Janet Yellen, who referred to a further reduction of the export of Iranian oil and sanctions that will be decided "in the coming days", the members of the Republican party who sit in the US Congress insist on the hard line towards Tehran.
<h2> What sanctions already applied
In the sight of American sanctions there is the Iranian nuclear program, the energy sectors (hydrocarbons) and defense, property and interests of members of the government and the pasdaran, including President Ebrahim Raisi, banks and finance, with relapses in different areas of the Iranian economy. Since 2020, sanctions have affected thousands of Iranian companies and legal persons. The United States has imposed sanctions on the Iranian Atomic Energy Organization and several other institutions that have collaborated on the development of the Iranian nuclear program, including dozens of banks, including the Central Bank of Iran.
&nbsp;
In Washington, also the Ministry of Oil of Tehran, the Iranian National Oil Company and companies that share the profits of crude oil. The sanctions have also come to strike Chinese companies and the Arab Emirates, finished in the sight for having concluded business with the ayatollah regime. To be put under pressure through the freezing of property, funds and investments also the pasdaran, the military body of the guardians of the Revolution, the special forces Quds, the Ministry of Defense. Both pasdaran and special forces Quds are also considered by the US terrorist organizations.
&nbsp;
<div </div
<h2> New incoming sanctions
In the light of the measures already applied the American government, as anticipated by the Treasury, studies to make even more complicated the export of Iranian oil and to stagnate lenders and financiers through which Iran manages to bypass sanctions. The first move of the White House plans to increase pressure on the European Union, so that it imposes the same package of sanctions that at the moment, so extensively, is applied only by the US.
&nbsp;
In 2018 then President Donald Trump returned to impose sanctions previously suspended, following the dialogue on nuclear power by the administration of his predecessor Barack Obama. The debate has come to this day, the Republicans sitting at the congress accused President Joe Biden of failing to strike Iran and want more stringent measures. The Republicans now call for more powers to control the derogations to sanctions and widen the ban on exporting to Iran to other products, including technology. Republicans press for derogues to be considered more carefully to prevent terrorist activities.
&nbsp;
On Monday, Parliament adopted an amendment entitled "Sanctions to Iran and China on energy", which will allow Iran to strike further. The law requires the preparation of an annual report on energy trade between China and Iran in order to determine which Chinese financial institutions have done business with Tehran. Once identified, it will be forbidden to conclude business with US counterparts. The law is now in the wake of the Senate, where the Democrats have the majority. The Foreign Commission of the Senate has approved an amendment to strike ports and refineries from which oil passes, violating sanctions. To be enforced, sanctions require the approval of the Senate and the subsequent signature of President Biden.
<h2> Scope of sanctions
"American sanctions to Iran constitute the largest and largest package of sanctions applied by the United States," reads in a report by Congressional Research Service. The sanctions applied practically zeroed trade between Tehran and Washington, frozen Iranian investment in the US and prohibited sale of weapons and components. In addition to the attacks on Israel, the White House points its finger at Iran's nuclear program, respect for human rights and support of Ayatollahs to groups such as Hezbollah, Hamas and Yemeni Houthi.
&nbsp;
The US sanctions until now have had heavy consequences on the Iranian population and, of course, on companies in the country. The White House wants the regime to change the register, people in Iran is striated by a tremendous economic crisis and as a result the Iranian society suffers from a split between the regime and the population ever deeper. In recent parliamentary elections, turnout was around 40%. &nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;

